aps, Google Chrome etc. pretty smoothly through the Go Edition.','5,890','10'),('Mobile','Symphony','PT-000028','Symphony V141','  Symphony V141 is a low-budget 3G smartphone running on Android 8.1 Oreo Go version. It has decent quality front and back cameras, satisfactory performance for day to day usage, satisfactory battery backup, dual SIM, decent front and back cameras etc. features. It is altogether a good deal considering the price. The phone doesnâ€™t come with OTG support and fingerprint sensor which can be seen as drawbacks. There is also no Full HD video recording option. The FWVGA+ screen helps to get longer battery backup, but quality wise, HD+ screen would have been a much more appreciated feature. So, it has some fine advantages in this price range, but you must consider that a few important features are missing.','4,890','10'),('Mobile','Symphony','PT-000029','Symphony i97','  Symphony i97 is coming with Android 9 Pie version. It has a fine quality 13 MP back camera which supports portrait mode or bokeh effect (also called background blur or DSLR mode). The 8 MP front camera is a pretty adequate deal as well. The device is running on a powerful 1.6 GHz octa-core CPU and 2 GB RAM. It means multitasking should be very smooth. High graphics game like PUBG can be played with low settings in this smartphone.\r\n\r\nSymphony i97 comes with a highly demanding fingerprint sensor at an attractive price. It also supports 4G. The battery is a decent 3200 mAh one. 5.7 inches HD+ IPS full-view screen is among the better ones around the price. The mysterious kind of gradient backside makes this phone more desirable. The gadget has 16 GB internal storage and an additional MicroSD card can be used to extend the memory up to 64 GB. Among other features there are face unlock, FM radio, dual Micro SIM, OTG and so on.','7,490','10'),('Mobile','Symphony','PT-000030','Symphony Z15','  Symphony Z15 is the first waterdrop notch display smartphone released by Symphony. 2.5D 